OL,3,CWales is better off now than before
OL,4,Cthe 1984 miners' strike, says Lord
OL,5,CHeseltine
OL,7,FITV Wales' asked him if he
OL,8,Facknowledged that the strike, and the
OL,9,Fsubsequent closure of mines in the
OL,10,F1990s when he was responsible for the
OL,11,Findustry as president of the Board of
OL,12,FTrade in John Major's government, had
OL,13,Fcaused permanent damage to communities
OL,14,Fin Wales.
OL,16,FIn response, he said: "There's been an
OL,17,Fadjustment, certainly, but into better
OL,18,Fjobs in a cleaner and healthier and
OL,19,Fless dangerous atmosphere. So if you
OL,20,Fsay to me, 'would I recreate the
OL,21,Fmining industry?' No, I would not."
