OL,7,F"But if anyone should apologise, it's
OL,8,Fthe militancy in the unions who made
OL,9,Fcoal production uneconomic."
OL,11,FIn the interview, he said that despite
OL,12,Fcoming from a privileged background he
OL,13,Funderstood the strength of feeling in
OL,14,FWelsh coal communities.
OL,16,F"I have a great admiration for the
OL,17,Fcommunity spirit in the mining
OL,18,Fvillages and towns. I myself lived in
OL,19,Fa relatively prosperous part of
OL,20,FSwansea.
